25|$|The {{idea of a}} <b>spherical</b> <b>Earth</b> {{appeared}} in Greek philosophy with Pythagoras (6th century BC), although most pre-Socratics (6th – 5th century BC) retained the flat Earth model. Aristotle provided evidence for the spherical shape of the Earth on empirical grounds by around 330 BC. Knowledge of the <b>spherical</b> <b>Earth</b> gradually began to spread beyond the Hellenistic world from then on.|$|R
